---
title: Smoky & Spicy White Bean Toasts with Tomato & Arugula Salad
description: For this simple, quick, and satisfying vegetarian lunch, you’ll use the classic Spanish technique of rubbing cut garlic cloves on toast to extract flavor (without too much of that raw garlic punch). You’ll use this clever garlic toast as a vehicle for warm, smoky, hearty beans topped with juicy tomato and finished with an arugula, pecan, and honey mustard salad. Beans on toast with tangy-sweet greens on top? Now that’s one tasty way to get a wholesome dish on the table in just ten minutes!
